        "comment": "The avalanche risk is moderate above 1600 metres and low below. Wet snow is the problem. Gliding avalanches can occur on a few steep slopes with a smooth surface, such as meadow slopes or rock slabs. In addition, wet loose snow or slab avalanches can release themselves on extremely steep terrain or be triggered by individuals on very steep terrain. The avalanches reach medium size.",
        "highlights": "The snowpack is soaked right up to the highest peaks."
